Hannah Bluck, 18, from Porthcawl, south Wales, was diagnosed with Avascular necrosis in her distal tibia in March 2013 .
The rare condition has caused her weight-bearing shin bone to die from lack of oxygen .
She has played for the Wales youth national teams at U19, U17 and U16 level .
Doctors have been baffled by the rare condition, which has never been seen on a leg bone and usually affects joints .